title: Two To The Power Of Love
subject: Attraction
notes: Only Released in Europe and UK Sept 84 as 2nd single from Janets 2nd LP. Terrible cheap cover thrown together, https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Two_to_the_Power_of_Love#/media/File:Two_The_Power_of_Love.jpeg  Janet 17 studio promo shot juxtaposed with Cliff 44 shot in front of a hedge looking away to the right off the cover away from Janet, seems like a staged papparazzi shot. Produced by peak soundtrack Moroder (Flashdance, Scarface, Electric Dreams, Neverending Story) https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XVvZ4-dTd64  Joe espositos scarface sing-a-long. The comedown after Moroder and Esposito's (with help from Donna Summer) disco triumph Heaven Knows https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BcHciz6eeeI Written by Pete Beckett and Steve Kipner. Why Cliff? Janet was trying to break free from Joe as he was guiding her career making artistic and commercial decisions (CLIFF?) she didn´t want to be in Fame TV show. she eloped with James DeBarge of Debarge another family Musical group with a history of physical abuse, in September 84 but the marriage only lasted a year before annulment due to his pain killer addiction. Two of his brothers got done for drug trafficking in the late 80s. Cliff is hitting his silver jubilee and bases a release around it and does lots of TV with 'Please don´t fall in love' and 'Baby, you´re dynamite' https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dG-uQswyZBA , a couple of duets just prior to this one rocker with Phil Everly 'She Means nothing to me' and one synth ballad with fellow gawd sqwuader Sheila Walsh 'Drifting' https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=96Iqz-SGgL0  but maybe it is Cliff's success with ONJ in 80 with Suddenly from Xanadu, written by John Farrar of 'You´re the one that i want' 78. Farrar uses Steve Kipner on ONJ Physical album 81, Beckett & Kipner joint songwriting credit ONJ Twist of Fate 83  bandmates from Tin Tin and then Skyband https://peterbeckett-player.com/credits Tin Tin were produced by Maurice Gibb. a studio session with Maurice Gibb doing a John Lennon impression was released as 'Have you Heard the Word' by The Fut in 70 as a fake beatles bootleg. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hXBZp_PvQjA https://peterbeckett-player.com/think-out-loud  Beckett best known for his late 70s smooth rock band Player and hit song Baby Come Back https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Hn-enjcgV1o  Tried his hand at a duet a year previous with Beckett & Nelson https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Cu1CGyrFmjo Featured on Fame (without Cliff) around time of release https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Fmju6js6qyE  After this she gets rid of Joe and starts working with producers Jimmy Jam & Terry Lewis of the Time band, who performed Prince Material.

First performed together at Live Aid 85 with errrr '...and Mr Andrew Ridgely' https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ECN_wgw55lc George is very excited for his moment he looks suprised Andrew is on his tail. George added some backing vocals on Nikita in the same year. in  91 he performed his Cover to Cover tour, singing lots of.... covers. a couple of which were ELTs https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cover_to_Cover_tour George prefers control and makes use of the audience to up the spectacle with the unveiling 3 mins in https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RsKqMNDoR4o  no conversation as a duet, just doubling of lines with ad libs, pretty faithful to the arrangment from 74, guitar harmonics in place (Davey Johnstone). But no Beach boys in the choir. Bettered the original release being a global hit. Before it George had not promoted his last album Listen Without Prejudice Vol.1. (What a turn off of a title, no wonder he rubbed people the wrong way) and not appearing in videos (instead employing supermodels https://www.biography.com/news/george-michael-freedom-90-song-music-video#:~:text=growth%20for%20Michael-,The%20%22Freedom!,referenced%20one%20of%20his%20Wham! ). Praying for time his Lennon ´on the nose' political anthem with subtitles on a black background echoing sign of the times but lacking style. hubris, Freedom 90 exploited the piano house electronic keyboards that Happy Mondays and Primal Scream had previously and going meta with the leather jacket from Faith image burning.  After he had years of litigation with Sony that stifled his career until 96. Elton used his recently new lower range to his advantage with the following year´s muscular duet Runaway Train with guess who....CLAPTON. Lethal weapon 3 credit song and maxi single with.... title: Slow Rivers

notes:
Tough analogy to crack. Slow rivers run cold (dumb people are cold hearted?) shallow waters never sank so low (water would never degrade itself?). weather, water, dogs in fog. On a tv performance Cliff introduces it as Cold rivers to confirm the confusion, he doubles down during an interview  "Elton and I made a record, a pretty good record too. It wasn't a hit. Did you hear that one? Elton John? It was called Cold Rivers. [sic] Good song. Good record, actually. But it didn't catch the imagination of the public. You know, that's the problem. But nevertheless it's a good record."
Cliff Richard http://www.cliffrichardsongs.com/popup.php?data=SlowRivers198410_popupplus  also calls Elton ELT in a familiar way.. mid 70´s Cliff released on Elton´s label Rocket Records, Cliff was called ''Sylvia'' because he used to ring up the office each week, asking if his record had gone silver yet.
